    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A Garou can assume multiple sacred forms, each representing a balance between human, wolf, and spirit</p><p>These forms alter how the Garou interacts with the world, affecting combat presence, social impact, movement, and spiritual resonance.</p><p>The Garou’s forms include:</p><p>• Homid – Human form</p><p>• Glabro – Near-human war form</p><p>• Crinos – War form of legend</p><p>• Hispo – Dire wolf form</p><p>• Lupus – Natural wolf form</p><p>Each form has unique strengths, limitations, and interactions with Rage, Gnosis, and Delirium. The effects of each form are defined by additional Garou features.</p><p></p>",
